ROUTE OF THE Orient Star
Interesting and useful information
for world travelers.
Few travel experiences can equal the fascination and
interest of a trip along Philippine Air Lines' "Route of
the Orient Star."
Stopping at fourteen cities in eleven
countries, the traveler along this route is treated to an
extravaganza of scenic beauty, history, architecture, racial
customs and national cultures. Here, indeed, is a pano-
rama of contrasts: The new world and the old, oriental
and occidental,
tropical and temperate climates, vast
oceans and towering mountains.
Whether you travel for business or pleasure
or both
— you will want to extract the full measure of interest
and enjoyment from your trip.
This booklet has been
prepared to help you do this — to provide you with a
"thumbnail sketch" of what awaits you along the "Route
of the Orient Star."
Included are practical tips con-
cerning attire, accommodations and local transportation
facilities.
Also included are general maps of the areas
you will visit and interesting data about the major cities
of the world.
Should you desire further information to help you pre-
pare for your trip, your Travel Agent or any Philippine
Air Lines Office will be pleased to furnish it. If you
require assistance en route, remember that every P. A. L.
representative is trained and eager to serve you.
